Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery cup of hemispherical shape; pale orange clay with white inclusions; glaze fired orangde; interior glazed; exterior: three bands painted on lower wall and narrow band at top of lip; inscription cut on exterior, in reserved zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.364)
